title: Electron launches second pair of NASA TROPICS cubesats
summary: A Rocket Lab Electron rocket launched a second pair of NASA storm-tracking cubesats late May 25, six years and three dozen flights after the company’s first orbital launch attempt.

title: NASA safety panel skeptical of Starliner readiness for crewed flight
summary: The chair of a NASA safety panel urged the agency not to rush into a crewed test flight of Boeing’s CST-100 Starliner vehicle, calling for an independent “deep look” at technical issues with the spacecraft.

title: Orbit Fab selects Impulse Space’s orbital vehicle for in-space refueling demo
summary: Orbit Fab announced May 25 it selected an orbital vehicle made by startup Impulse Space to host a fuel depot for an in-orbit refueling demonstration funded by the U.S. military.

title: A new report finds NASA has spent an obscene amount of money on SLS propulsion
summary: "NASA and its contracts will continue to exceed planned cost and schedule."

title: Kleos enters partnership with General Atomics
summary: Kleos Space announced a partnership with General Atomics Commonwealth Computer Research aimed at making it easier for analysts around the world to derive insights from Kleos’ radio frequency data.
